HEADWORD: Logographer
<hw>Lo*gog"ra*pher</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
chronicler; one who writes history in a condensed manner with short
simple sentences.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One skilled in logography.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

